True or False? With DNS failover, if a record set fails a health check, it will be removed from the Route 53 response until it passes the health check.

True

Correct Answer
DNS Failover consists of two components: health checks and failover. Health checks are automated requests sent over the Internet to your application to verify that your application is reachable, available, and functional. With DNS failover, if a record set fails a health check, it will be removed from the Route 53 response until it passes the health check. Health Checks & DNS Failover.
https://aws.amazon.com/route53/faqs/#Health_Checks_.26_DNS_Failover

